import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data.sort_values(by='year')
    plt.plot(data['year'], data['pop'])
    plt.title('What is the trend of population over the years?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Population')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    plt.scatter(data['fertility'], data['life_expect'])
    plt.xlabel('Fertility Rate')
    plt.ylabel('Life Expectancy')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between life expectancy and fertility rate?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.sort_values(by='life_expect', ascending=False)
    plt.bar(data['country'], data['life_expect'])
    plt.title('Which country has the highest life expectancy?', wrap=True)
    plt.axhline(y=data['life_expect'].max(), color='r', linestyle='-',
                label=f"Max life expectancy: {data['life_expect'].max():.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['fertility'].plot(kind='hist', bins=30, color='green', alpha=0.5)
    plt.axvline(data['fertility'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Median = {:.2f}'.format(data['fertility'].median()))
    plt.title('What is the distribution of fertility rate?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.groupby(['cluster'])['pop'].sum().reset_index()
    plt.bar(data['cluster'], data['pop'])
    plt.title('How does the population of countries in different clusters compare?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Cluster')
    plt.ylabel('Population')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
